         <abstract>
            <p>A Test Suite (TS) is typically a collection of Natural Language sentences against which the coverage of a Natural Language Processing system can be evaluated. We describe a method by which such suites can be produced automatically, involving a modification and extension of the Definite Clause Grammar formalism, and describe some of the advantages of the method over the traditional method of manual construction.</p>
         </abstract>
